First, you need to have any distro of linux, then install Podman or Docker. You can pull this image by: 
podman pull 
Check the image if it's saved on your Linux server or not by: podman images ps
After that, copy the entrypoint.sh , is a shell script that serves as the containerâ€™s entrypoint.
It tells the container what to do when it starts. It is used to initialize services or configurations before the container fully starts.
fully starts.
Entrypoint in FreeIPA Context:
For your FreeIPA container, the entrypoint typically needs to:
1.	Handle first-time initialization
2.	Start necessary services
3.	Manage the lifecycle of the IPA server
you can edit the entrypoint.sh file with your own arguments.


